  "definitions": [
    "to refer (to direct to a source for help or information)",
    "to relate (to tell in a descriptive way)",
    "to refer (submit to an authority figure for consideration)",
    "to be about something; to have something as a subject\nEsta lei refere-se aos crimes de fraude e extorsão.\nThis law is about the crimes of fraud and racketeering.",
    "to refer (to allude to)"
  ],
  "description": "referir (first-person singular present indicative refiro, past participle referido)",
  "etymology": "From Old Portuguese referir, from Latin referō (“I carry back”).",
